cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.AI 

The paper deals with the application of graph signal processing to neuroimaging datasets, which involves machine learning techniques for classification and dimensionality reduction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper also involves signal processing and graph theory, which could fall under cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively.
